{"lemma":"سُكَّرُ","slug":"سُكَّرُ","root":"س.ك.ر","root_slug":"س-ك-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/س-ك-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"سُكَّرُ","root":"سكر","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":7,"pos_tags":["adj","noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":13},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n20213","n20218","n20219","n20220","n20221","n20222","n20228"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B3%D9%8F%D9%83%D9%8E%D9%91%D8%B1%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"sugar","tags":["uncountable"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to sugar, to sprinkle sugar over"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to sweeten, to add sugar"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to candy"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to get drunk, to become intoxicated"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be drunk, to be intoxicated"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"intoxicant"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"wine"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of سَكِرَ (sakira) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"drunkenness, intoxication, inebriety"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of سَكِرَ (sakira) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"drunk"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"alternative form of سُكَّار (sukkār, “bolt-lock”)","tags":["alt-of","alternative"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Etymology tree\nProto-Indo-European *ḱorkeh₂\nProto-Indo-Iranian *ćárkaraH\nProto-Indo-Aryan *śárkaraH\nSanskrit शर्क॑रा (śárkarā)\nGandhari 𐨭𐨐𐨪 (śakara)bor.\nMiddle Persian 𐭱𐭪𐭥 (šakar)bor.\nArabic سكر\nBorrowed from Middle Persian 𐭱𐭪𐭥 (šakar), borrowed from Gandhari 𐨭𐨐𐨪 (śakara), from Sanskrit शर्क॑रा (śárkarā), from Proto-Indo-Aryan *śárkaraH, from Proto-Indo-Iranian *ćárkaraH, from Proto-Indo-European *ḱorkeh₂ (“gravel”). For the vocalism from Middle Persian to Arabic, compare أُشَّق (ʔuššaq, “ammoniacum”).\n\nFrom Proto-Semitic *šikar- (“alcoholic drink”). Cognate with Hebrew שֵׁכָר (šēḵār)."},"ipa":["/suk.kar/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n20213","headword_ar":"سَكِرَ","root":"skr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sakarN","text_ar":"سَكَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sukorN","text_ar":"سُكْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A, Mgh, K,) or this is a simple subst., (S, Msb,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sukurN","text_ar":"سُكُرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sakorN","text_ar":"سَكْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sikarN","text_ar":"سِكَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sakaraAnN","text_ar":"سَكَرَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, intoxicated, inebriated,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"drunken;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(MA, KL, &c.;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaHaA","text_ar":"صَحَا"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, A, K.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sukorN","text_ar":"سُكْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", below.] ―         -b2-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sakira EalaY~afulaAnN","text_ar":"سَكِرَ عَلَىَّفُلَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sakarN","text_ar":"سَكَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, violently angry with me:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"angry;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"enraged."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lahu EalaY~a sakarN","text_ar":"لَهُ عَلَىَّ سَكَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He has violent anger against me."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sakirato A^aboSaArunaA","text_ar":"سَكِرَتْ اَبْصَارُنَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sakirat A^aboSaAru Alqawomi","text_ar":"سَكِرَت اَبْصَارُ القَوْمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sakirato Eayonuhu","text_ar":"سَكِرَتْ عَيْنُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see 2. ―         -b4-  Also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sakira","text_ar":"سَكِرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (TK,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sakarN","text_ar":"سَكَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (IAar, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a wateringtrough, or tank, TK)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, full."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, K, TK.) ―         -b5-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sakirati Alr~iyHu","text_ar":"سَكِرَتِ الرِّيحُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A, and so in my MS. copy of the K,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sakarat","text_ar":"سَكَرَت"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, and so in the CK,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O,) or, as some relate a verse of Jendel Ibn-El-Muthennà Et- Tuhawee, in which it occurs,"},{"kind":"text","text":", (O,) [indicating that the pret. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sakirat","text_ar":"سَكِرَت"},{"kind":"text","text":"or that the aor. is irreg.,] inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sukuwrN","text_ar":"سُكُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sakaraAnN","text_ar":"سَكَرَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The wind became still,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, O, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"after blowing."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sakara","text_ar":"سَكَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sakira","text_ar":"سَكِرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sukuwrN","text_ar":"سُكُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(water)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became still, ceasing to run:"},{"kind":"text","text":"so says AZ: and (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it"},{"kind":"text","text":"(the sea)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became calm,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"motionless:"},{"kind":"text","text":"so says IAar. (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sakira","text_ar":"سَكِرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sakara","text_ar":"سَكَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(food [in a cooking-pot], or hot water, A, or a hot thing, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ceased to boil,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"estuate,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to burn,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"be hot:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it"},{"kind":"text","text":"(heat)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became allayed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it subsided."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sakarahu","text_ar":"سَكَرَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see 4. ―         -b2-  Also, (IAar, TA,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (TK,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sakorN","text_ar":"سَكْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He filled it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, K, * TA.) ―         -b3-  Also, (S, Mgh, Msb,) aor. as above, (S, Msb,) and so the inf. n.; (S, Mgh, Msb, K;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sk~rhu","text_ar":"سكّرهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tasokiyrN","text_ar":"تَسْكِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (MF;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He stopped it up,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dammed it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"namely, a river, or rivulet. (S, Mgh, Msb, K, MF.) And hence,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sakara AlbaAba","text_ar":"سَكَرَ البَابَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sk~rhu","text_ar":"سكّرهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He closed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stopped up, the door."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sukirato A^aboSaArunaA","text_ar":"سُكِرَتْ اَبْصَارُنَا"},{"kind":"text","text":": see 2."}],"source_refs":["S","Mgh","Msb","K","A","TK","IAar","O","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n20218","headword_ar":"سَكْرٌ","root":"skr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sakoraAnu","text_ar":"سَكْرَانُ"},{"kind":"text","text":":       -A2-  and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sikorN","text_ar":"سِكْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".       -A3-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain herb,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"leguminous plant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baqolapN","text_ar":"بَقْلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of such as are termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHoraAr","text_ar":"اَحْرَار"},{"kind":"text","text":"[pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hur~N","text_ar":"حُرٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (Aboo-Nasr, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which is of the best of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buquwl","text_ar":"بُقُول"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA as from the K: [but not in my MS. copy of the K nor in the CK:]) AHn says that no description of its general attributes or qualities had come to his knowledge. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n20219","headword_ar":"سُكْرٌ","root":"skr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"an inf. n., (A, Mgh, K,) or a simple subst., signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Intoxication, inebriation,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"drunkenness;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e. the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"state thereof;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a state that intervenes as an obstruction between a man and his intellect;"},{"kind":"text","text":"mostly used in relation to intoxicating drinks: but sometimes as meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such a state arising from anger,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from the passion of love:"},{"kind":"text","text":"a poet says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"sukoraAni sukoru hawFY wasukoru mudaAmapK\n                      \n                     \n                        A^an~aY yufiyqu fatFY bihi sukoraAni"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Two intoxications, the intoxication of love and the intoxication of wine: how shall a youth recover his senses in whom are two intoxications?"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Er-Rághib, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["A","Mgh","K"]},{"entry_id":"n20220","headword_ar":"سِكْرٌ","root":"skr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"a subst. from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~akoru","text_ar":"السَّكْرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, K) as meaning “ the stopping up, or damming, ” of the river, or rivulet; (K;) i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A dam; a thing with which a river,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rivulet, is stopped up;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * Msb, K, TA;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sakorN","text_ar":"سَكْرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", originally an inf. n., occurs in the same sense: (Mgh:) the pl. of the former is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sukuwrN","text_ar":"سُكُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.)"}],"source_refs":["Mgh","K"]},{"entry_id":"n20221","headword_ar":"سَكَرٌ","root":"skr","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Wine:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) so, accord. to Fr and others in the Kur [xvi. 69],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tat~axi*uwna minohu sakarFA warizoqFA HasanFA","text_ar":"تَتَّخِذُونَ مِنْهُ سَكَرًا وَرِزْقًا حَسَنًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ye obtain therefrom wine, and raisins and dried dates and the like;"},{"kind":"text","text":"this being said before wine was prohibited: (TA:) and the ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beverage called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nabiy*","text_ar":"نَبِيذ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"prepared from dried dates:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) so in the Kur, ubi suprà: (S:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"expressed juice of fresh ripe dates when it has become strong;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb;) originally an inf. n.: (Mgh:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an infusion of dried dates, untouched by fire:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A 'Obeyd:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a beverage,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nabiy*","text_ar":"نَبِيذ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made from dried dates and from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ka$uwv","text_ar":"كَشُوث"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a species of cuscuta,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dodder"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (A, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and myrtle,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=s","text_ar":"ا=س"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A,) which is the most bitter beverage in the world, (A,) and forbidden like wine; (TA;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made from dried dates and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"k$wv","text_ar":"كشوث"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"disposed layer upon layer, upon which water is poured;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and some assert that"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sometimes myrtle"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=s","text_ar":"ا=س"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is mixed with it, and this increases its strength:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AHn:) also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"anything that intoxicates:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what is forbidden"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that is obtained"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from fruit"},{"kind":"text","text":"(I'Ab, T, K) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the palm-tree and grape vine"},{"kind":"text","text":"], meaning wine, before its being forbidden; and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~izoqu AlHasanu","text_ar":"الرِّزْقُ الحَسَنُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is what is lawful [that is obtained] from grapes and dates: (I 'Ab, T, TA:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vinegar;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;) accord. to some of the expositors of the Kur, ubi suprà; but this is a meaning unknown to the leading lexicologists: (B, TA:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"food:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) so accord. to AO alone; as in the following saying of a poet;"},{"kind":"quote","text":"jaEalota A^aEoraADa AlkiraAmi sakaraA"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thou hast made the reputations of the generous to be food:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thou hast made the vituperation of the generous to be food to thee:"},{"kind":"text","text":"but the leading lexicologists disallow this; and Zj says that the more probable meaning here is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wine."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["K","TA","S","A","Mgh","AHn","B"]},{"entry_id":"n20222","headword_ar":"سَكِرٌ","root":"skr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sakoraAnu","text_ar":"سَكْرَانُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": ―         -b2-  and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sikiyrN","text_ar":"سِكِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n20228","headword_ar":"سُكَّرٌ","root":"skr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Sugar;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain sweet substance,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"well known:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, TA:) a Pers. word, (S,) arabicized, (S, K,) from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$akaro","text_ar":"شَكَرْ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) n. un. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a piece of sugar"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S, K:) it is hot and moist, accord. to the most correct opinion; but some say, cold: and the best sort of it is the transparent, called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tabaroza*N","text_ar":"طَبَرْزَذٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and the old is more delicate than the new: it is injurious to the stomach, engendering yellow bile; but the juice of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layomuwn","text_ar":"لَيْمُون"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naAranoj","text_ar":"نَارَنْج"},{"kind":"text","text":"counteract its noxiousness: it is said to be a word recently introduced; but some say that it occurs in one trad. (TA.) ―         -b2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suk~ar","text_ar":"سُكَّر"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sugar"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in sweetness:"},{"kind":"text","text":"so used by Aboo-Ziyád El-Kilábee. (TA.) ―         -b3-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain kind of sweet fresh ripe dates;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a sort of fresh ripe dates, likened to sugar in sweetness:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a kind of very sweet dates;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AHát, T, Msb;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"known to the people of ElBahreyn,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and in Sijilmáseh and Dar'ah, and, as some say, in El-Medeeneh, where, how-"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1392},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ever, they require to be dried artificially."},{"kind":"text","text":"(MF.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A kind of grapes, which, being affected by what is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maraq","text_ar":"مَرَق"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fall off,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for the most part: their bunches are of middling size; and they are white, juicy, and very sweet,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the best kinds of grapes;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and are made into raisins."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["TA","Msb","S","K","Mgh","T"]}]}}